reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Rich, Creamy, Lovely Moisturizer
reviews.reviewText: Since I just received this yesterday, I've no way of knowing about the long term benefits of the hyaluronic acid and peptides, but it can't hurt to have them in there. What I mainly wanted was the moisturizer with sunscreen. So far I'm loving this. First of all, the packaging is very nice in the glass bottle, and when it gets low the cap twists off easily. The pump dispenses just the right amount at a time. The cream itself is so rich and silky smooth, it spreads easily and absorbs beautifully without feeling greasy. The scent is also very nice, nothing heavy or overpowering. My face feels amazing, soft and super moisturized, and God knows I need that! Very pleased with my purchase, I plan to incorporate this into my morning routine and will continue to purchase. Their customer service is also amazing should you have any questions, very helpful and quick to respond.

reviews.reviewText: This is a nice, rich protective moisturizer. Using retinol and living in Florida I need SPF for walking my dog. I put this on and it protects me. Nice and moisturizing too

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality for Price
reviews.reviewText: Great quality skin care for the price point! Is really light and non-oily for an SPF 30, which I struggle to find. Scent is very natural and not overwhelming. Packaging is also very nice and seems more sustainable than other companies

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wonderful SPF moisturizer not greasy! I’m combo skin, age 54
reviews.reviewText: I love this moisturizer! I have some soft wrinkles, but I detest heavy day creams or greasy face look. This is just right! It’s light and has a creamy texture, has a delicate almost no scent smell which dissipates and dries quickly, leaves no white cast, feels dewy but satiny, never glossy. Cream foundation or powder foundation goes on smoothly. Skin looks beautiful all day! And I never get a blemish or clogged pores with this cream. My only complain is that though I love the pump mechanism, when it runs low it’s difficult to get whatever bit is left behind. For the price, it hurts to throw the pump out knowing that I may have two more days worth of cream left😣 Should come in a squeezable tube. Until then, I need to keep repurchasing, I’m hooked!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Works great but intermittently smells awful!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve ordered this a number of times and have generally been pleased. It goes on light and moisturizes great. I also appreciated the fact that it had a light pleasant fragrance. A few months back I got a bottle of it that smelled really off. It had a heavy petroleum smell to it that was unpleasant to put on. I thought maybe it was a one off and so I continued buying. Fast forward to now and I have just started using a new bottle. It has the same off putting odor to it (lot D12T4, exp 04/24). It stinks to the point I can’t continue using it. Reading other reviews, it seems I’m not the only purchaser that’s had this problem. I’ll be looking for another product that can be more consistent with the quality of what they send. This is a shame because I really enjoy this product, but I don’t want to spend money only to get the occasional surprise stink bomb.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great replacement for higher priced product!
reviews.reviewText: I started using anti-aging face products about 20 years ago. Back then you bought products from a certain doctor that did infomercials. The lotions/creams contained some kind of “special sauce” with magical ingredients that could only be obtained by buying those products. They were expensive, but they worked and I figured you get what you pay for.Nowadays, it seems like every company has essentially the same ingredients; the same vitamins, peptides, retinol, etc. There is no longer any secret sauce. It’s all just branding.One differentiator I became painfully aware of is cost. The products I had used for many years had become more expensive. They also were being sold in smaller containers! So less product for more money! It got to the point where I was paying $85 for a 0.5 ounce jar of Moisturizer with SPF! That was when I decided to find an alternative.I searched Amazon and found The Naeli Day Moisturizer. It had very good reviews at a very reasonable price. It’s been several months now since I started using the product and I have to say it is great! My fine lines are gone and wrinkles are less noticeable! What’s more, I live in Arizona and the SPF holds up well under the extremely sunny conditions we have here! I liked the product so much that I purchased the Naeli Night moisturizer, which I am also very happy with! They both have a nice texture; not heavy or too thick and have a pleasant smell. They go on smooth and absorb quickly into the skin. I’ve had no skin irritation or breakouts.These are high-quality products that work as advertised! I’m extremely pleased with my purchases and would highly recommend them!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works well, don't like the smell
reviews.reviewText: Works well as a moisturizer, and sun protector. However I hated the smell, it was like a burnt rosemary chemical smell. I liked the rosemary part, but the chemical smell was gross. I didn't return it because I did like it as a moisturizer/sunscreen. I could put my makeup over it without any issues. The smell does go away after an hour, so if you care bare a weird smell for a bit, I suppose its worth it.
